Ruth Buzzi https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ruth_Buzzi 0 Ruth Ann Buzzi (born July 24, 1936) is an American actress, comedian and singer. She has appeared onstage, as well as in films and television. She is best known for her performances on the comedy-variety show Rowan Martin's Laugh-In from 1968–73, for which she won a Golden Globe Award and received five Emmy nominations.
